Name: anterior foramen magnum meningioma
Definition: A skin melanoma that is characterized by slow growth of a small pigmented spot on the skin with a clearly defined edge
Synonym: meningioma of the Anterior Foramen Magnum

Name: obsolete recurrent childhood glioma of brain stem
Definition: A skin melanoma that is characterized by slow growth of a small pigmented spot on the skin with a clearly defined edge

Name: posterior foramen magnum meningioma
Definition: A disease of metabolism that is characterized by enzyme deficiency or accumulation of enzymes or toxins which interfere with normal function due to inherited enzyme abnormality.
Synonym: meningioma of the Posterior Foramen Magnum
